images.alt: Rest In Peace, Frankie. I love you.

I was watching Wall Street: Money Never Sleeps the other day and Gordon Gekko (Michael Douglas) has a line "Money isn't the prime asset in life, time is." That quote really fucked me up. I'm going to lose my grandfather any day, any hour, any minute now. I didn't grow up with a "mom and dad" I grew up with grandma and grandpa and he did everything humanly possible to make sure I lived as "normal" of a life as I could. Kept a roof over my head, cloths on my back, food in my stomach. More than anything, he spent as much TIME with me as he could. He never missed a single one of my football games; pee wee, high school, college. Not one. I don't really know where I'm going with this post and it's probably TMI but I felt obligated to share and hopefully inspire someone to spend more TIME with those that they love and cherish. Everyone has real life shit to deal with: work, bills, school, etc. but that stuff is always going to be there, the ones you love most won't be. So take advantage of every single day possible, even if it's a 30 second phone call because the last thing that you want to wish is that you would have spent more TIME with someone. Time is free, all it requires is effort. Love you, Frankie.
BFF

Happy birthday to my brother @jesseack from us recording in the closet of our apartment 5 years ago to living on your couch to playing around the world you always been there and always will, so proud of you, keep shining 2017

As I turn my back on 2016.  I'm not going to sit here and pretend how great 2016 was to me, I would be lying.
I released 0 Projects, 0 Visuals, 0 singles ,a couple of features and that's it. But that's not because I wanted it this way, it's because I was dealing with battles that were beyond my control. ________________________________
However, I am now finally free, free from everything that was restricting me both legally and mentally, I've taken the past few months to learn to produce so I never have to rely on anyone, and taken the time to really see who is there for me on this huge journey I'm about to embark on and I couldn't be more happier _____________________________
To everyone else I wish you a happy new year and to take time to realise who's actually there for you, because this year that was my most important lesson_________________________
a new project is in the works and a whole new version of Danny Seth is nearly completed 
_______________________________

2016 has been a milestone year for me. I was on a billboard in New York City thanks to @jumpman23 and @carmeloanthony, I was featured in the NBA @2k video game, I moved to Los Angeles (but I still travel a lot), I changed my company name, I trademarked my new logo, I upgraded my website, I expanded my services, I invested in a creative team, I invested in a legal team, I worked out of the country more, I invested in shirts with my own logo on them because MY brand is the most important brand in my life, I created opportunities for others, I executed every project at the highest level, I didn't let anyone hold me back (even when people flaked on me), I focused on what I can control, I showed up for every opportunity and I was hands-on with every booking. When creating LOE the mission wasn't ever to say I'm perfect...the mission was to attempt to put love within everything you do...weather that be in silence or when ppl are watching...that will forever be the goal. I've learned so much about self and life overall. I saw things that I liked and also things that i felt needed improvement on as well. We're almost two weeks into 2017 , and I hope it's going as planned for everyone as they intended on the 1st. Stay focused, plan and execute, be around those who help you grow not bring you down, stop comparing self to the next man or woman..all of our paths are different..so just do you and trust you'll be just fine. "It is our light, not our darkness that most frightens us...It is not in just some of us, it is in all of us. And as we let our own light shine, we unconsciously give other people permission to do the same. As we are liberated from our own fears, our presence automatically liberates others." - Marianne Williamson ‚ú®‚ú®‚ú®// Happy Friday loves! Feeling grateful for all the lights in my life who've helped me find my own light (many of you know who you are!) And thank you to all the people who have recently encouraged me to continue to share my journey of following my light and owning my truth. If I can inspire just ONE moment of presence, gratitude, peace, light, or love in just ONE person, I know I am living my purpose. üíûüíûüíû#FBF #LetYourLightShine

Last night was a full moon in Cancer, and I got to partake in a beautiful and totally impromptu energy clearing circle with new & old adopted family üíûüíûüíû Everyone took turns writing down things we'd be letting go of with this powerful full moon energy, and threw them into the fire to release ourselves from those things. It was the perfect reflection of how being open to the present leads you to your most fulfilling moments üôåüèæüôåüèæüôåüèæ How grateful I feel to find so many mates within the souls of those who are woven into my life! Last night I let go of: fear, anxiety, self-doubt, and self-judgement. Those are just some aspects of my Truth that I've been living, and am committed to letting go of. What will you let go of with this energy? What limiting beliefs or unhealthy habits will you release yourself from? I'd love to hear from you! Leave a comment or DM me if you feel it's too personal to share publicly. There's so much power in sharing your truth, even if it's not with me, I encourage you to share a piece of YOUR truth today with someone else.üôèüèæüôèüèæüôèüèæ

I promise to meditate. I promise to recite positive affirmations daily. I promise to be gentle during this process. I promise to explore. I promise to take better care of my body. I promise to read more. I promise to experience more.  I promise to write. I promise to create. I promise to shine brighter. I promise to be more vulnerable. I promise to love harder. I promise to take more risks. I promise to fall in love. I promise to breathe. I promise to sleep. I promise to protect. I promise to listen. I promise to give. I promise to stay grounded. I promise to talk to God on my good and bad days. I promise to befriend my fears. I promise to be selfish with my needs. I promise to take "can't" out of my personal dictionary. I promise to no longer doubt my abilities.I promise to be ok with not being ok.  I promise to get out of my comfort zone. I promise to become the best story teller I can.I promise to no longer procrastinate. I promise to put 100% in everything I do. I promise to not stress over the things I cannot change.I promise to be a better daughter. I promise to be a better friend. I promise to become a better business woman. I promise to treat everyone with kindness and respect. I promise to be the absolute best I can be. #ipromise #2017 #melanin #blackgirlmagic

-Liver cleansing from the gluconic acid, resulting in healthier skin & hair
-Increase of metabolism & resulting decrease of body fat from the healthy bacteria
Increase of energy from the oxygen rich brew
-Improved PH balance and resulting mental clarity from the alkaline nature of kombucha

You can try this Canadian made beverage at Shopper's Drugmart or check out their site www.tonicakombucha.com to find a store near you!

images.alt: Stop 8 on Nicky @Zimmermann's recent trip to #Marrakesh: "Sunset drinks on the rooftop at @elfennmarrakech are a great way to start off the evening. There are so many great places to eat in Marrakesh ‚Äî the list is endless. One of my favorites on thsi trip was Dar Yacout, a restaurant serving opulent Moroccan food paired with amazing ambience. Signing off from Marrakesh! x, Nicky" Stay tuned for our next T City Guide to Marrakesh, live on tmagazine.com tomorrow. Photo by Nicky Zimmermann.

Stop 7 on Nicky @Zimmermann's recent trip to #Marrakesh: "A trip to the Atlas Mountains is a great way to spend the day. The snow-capped peaks that you can see from the city are breathtaking, and the drive to get there is an experience in itself. A short hike and a quiet lunch at Riad Atlas Toubkal is a lovely way to take in the vast landscape." Photo by Nicky Zimmermann.

Stop 6 on Nicky @Zimmermann's recent trip to #Marrakesh: "Majorelle Garden (@officialjardinmajorelle) is one of the most visited places in the city, and for good reason. This stunning spot is filled with an eclectic mix of plants, and punctuated by the fountains and structures that were restored when the famed designer Yves Saint Laurent (@ysl) and his partner Pierre Berg√© purchased the land in 1980." images.alt: The current issue of #032c features a 36 page tour reportage on #RAMMSTEIN in the üá∫üá∏.... After beginning as castaways from the socialist bohemia of East Berlin, Rammstein‚Äôs 2012 Made in Germany tour was an authoritarian cabaret that asserted the revolutionary power of the grotesque. This is social critique in the form of fireballs spitting from steel batwings, of arenas filled with swaying smartphone lights. Even in this age of technological oversaturation, the spectacle of @rammsteinofficial remains over-powering. Their sound systems and pyrotechnics threaten to demolish the arenas that house them. Their lyrics are a shocking amalgam of poetry and militarism. Their story is a hangover of the 20th century. The band‚Äôs cross-country trip served as a strange sequel to the American arrival of Bertolt Brecht, Theodor Adorno, Ludwig Mies van der Rohe, and other German intellectuals fleeing Nazism more than 70 years prior: the deranged grandchildren of WWII parading through the land of exile, offering a twisted mockery of capitalism. üì∏ #andreasmuehe

A proposal by @melisapnr / CREATE YOUR OWN GEAR. If #032c lived by a single rule, it would have to be: Do it yourself. There simply is not enough time to sit around and wait for someone else to sort out your shit. Our 032c DIY BRANDING KIT is the manifestation of this belief. The tag comes with two safety pins for you to merchify your shirt, fur coat, bomber jacket, whatever. It is an authorized bootleg, if such a thing exists. Did we just dream that into being? See, that‚Äôs the spirit.

Move. Adapt. Protect. The NikeLab ACG collection is now available at the new NikeLab #Chicago and NikeLab #Tokyo stores, as well as select #NikeLab destinations worldwide. Shop the entire collection now at nike.com/nikelab.

By incorporating form, function and dependability into clean lines and minimalist aesthetics, @erlsn.acr and the NikeLab design team created a new ACG collection built on adaptability, movement and protection in the face of the city‚Äôs harshest conditions.
A technical take on the classic bomber, the ACG Metamorphosis Jacket provides protection thanks to 30D ripstop nylon with a durable water-repellant coating. The Thermore-insulated lining adds warmth while internal straps allow for off-shoulder wearing as you move throughout a city‚Äôs ever-changing environments. Four zip pockets add security and extra storage. The jacket also doubles as a liner by connecting to preexisting ACG shells.

ACG means all conditions gear and all conditions means all conditions. Available December 1 at the new NikeLab #Chicago and NikeLab #Tokyo, as well as select #NikeLab destinations worldwide and nike.com/nikelab.

The refined aesthetic of @erlsn.acr guides clean, minimalist design across the new NikeLab ACG collection. Made to move with its wearer through the harshest weather, ACG aids adaptation to the ever-changing city landscape with adjustable, extra-high collars and hoods, high-density pouches and device pockets, arm straps and snaps for off-shoulder wearing and ventilation‚Äîall in the name of increasing customization.

Built for ultimate winter adaptability, the System Blazer features a 3-in-1 configuration that includes a Nike AeroLoft-insulated liner for braving low temperatures or combining with previous ACG shells. The blazer‚Äôs collar unfolds to combine with the detachable hood for proper winter protection. The three-layer Gore-Tex¬Æ shell protects against wind and water yet stays breathable to keep the wearer warm and dry in the harshest weather.

Inventory: 2009-2016

After seven years, we‚Äôve decided to stop publishing Inventory. We‚Äôre extremely grateful to everyone that has supported the magazine by advertising with us or selling it in their stores; to those of you that have purchased a copy; and to the people and brands that have helped to bring our pages to life over the course of thirteen issues.

Making this magazine has been such a valuable experience. The lessons learned, knowledge gained, and relationships cemented could never be replaced, and it‚Äôs a journey that I‚Äôll remember forever. Due to the content and the people involved, it‚Äôs been a very personal project from the start, and I have to say the biggest thank you to my colleagues along the way. I want to acknowledge the pivotal work of Simon Roe from the beginning to the very end, as well as the roles played by Philip Watts and Owen Parrott, Stephen Mann and Anthony Hooper, Matthew Klassen and Chris Allen. Without your dedication Inventory would not have reached the same heights.

I look back on the legacy of what we‚Äôve created with awe and pride, but the publishing landscape has shifted and it feels like the right time to move on, to conclude things with arguably our best issue, and pursue new challenges and opportunities.

Sincerely,
Ryan Willms

Rural naturalism is a nineteenth century painting movement characterized by scenes of rural life and painted in a realist manner. The focus on sentimentalism of the rural naturalist artists distinguishes their work from the more gritty realist work of the nineteenth century.

Looking for a new feel-good account to follow? Leah Goren (@leahreenagoren) has got you covered. The Brooklyn-based artist's feed is rife with beautiful images made to inspire. From colorful illustrations of people to feminist ceramics and pins, Leah's photos are bound to put a grin on your face. "I'm usually moved to post when I'm excited about what I'm doing," she says. "It could be a crop in on some colors or shapes that make me feel really good as I'm drawing, a new project I'm proud of, or the way some of my handmade ceramics fit into my home decor." Speaking of projects, Leah is also the artistic brains behind two amazing books: ‚ÄòBESTIES‚Äô, which depicts the beauty of female friendship, and ‚ÄòLadies Drawing Night‚Äô, which she says "shows women how to host their own drawing nights through project ideas and inspiration.‚Äù It‚Äôs not always easy to pinpoint  what you want to achieve through your ‚Äògram, but Leah seems sure of one thing: "If I can make a stranger happy for a short moment with something beautiful I made, I think that is enough." ‚ú® We couldn't agree more. livejn.description: ‚Ä¢To Create Art That Inspires‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢To Make Deep Human Connections‚Ä¢ Turn on post notifications! - Let's work together!

images.alt:
We all need a wolfpack. A group of friends or family that we know we can rely on nomatter what. These are the people we love the most. They are the people that make our lives worth living. Right now I'm in a place where I feel like I have nobody fully on my side, like I am completely alone. Maybe it's the harsh realization of adulthood maybe it's the people that I surround myself with, I don't really know. All I can do is say cheers to the ones who are always there for us. Cheers to the ones who will never make us feel alone. The best idea I have on how to find them is to be one myself but I fear the letdowns that comes with. I guess we'll see if it works as we all should have the courage to try this out. Be the kind of person that is always reliable and always loving. You may get disappointed from time to time but right now it seems to me that the best way to find infallible love is to give it yourself. There's too much uncertainty in our lives as it is. Thank you all for the support you've given to me. Every inch of positivity you've given builds miles in my heart. I can't wait to give back once I'm ready.
.

images.alt: Windy City. Deep dish pizza. Crazy views. Photography. Chicago was good w/@troykazlauskas

I have a special place for this photo. It brings me back to when I was traveling in Kyrgyzstan last summer. We were driving on horrible roads for hours when we came upon this huge valley, and down below was a family and their home.
-
After sitting and talking with them, eating their home-made jam and bread, and drinking horse milk, they showed us around the valley. They only lived with the bare necessities of life. No luxuries. And hours and hours away from the nearest town. I've experienced this kind of lifestyle all over the world countless times, but it was different his time and I didn't know why.
-
I got to snap a few photos while the daughter was milking the horse as the father stoodby. Maybe it was the look in his face that got me...as if you could see into his eyes of all he's been through. All the highs and lows of life glowed on his face for a brief second...and he smiled, just after I took the photo. Something I can barely explain, yet won't forget.
You've got to go whole heart

There is hope and we can work on this together... one barber at a time. You may dislike me for this post, but this is how I feel. What we do need to change in our culture, is the higher advanced barbers (well known barbers) to change their attitude when speaking with the beginner barbers. It irritates me to watch barbers not acknowledge incoming barbers. I think to myself, "Like,WTF is wrong with you?" I make it a point to have a genuine conversation with EVERY person I speak with. chrisburkard.name: ChrisBurkard
chrisburkard.description: Have Camera, Will Travel. LDS‚Ä¢Photographer‚Ä¢Speaker‚Ä¢Director‚Ä¢Author Under An Arctic Sky Film trailer üëáüèº

images.alt:
Big Deep Breath. We spend too much time convincing ourselves that it could have been better or it wasn't as good as it could have been. Those thoughts can really crush the experience in the present moment. Photographers are the worst at it.. constantly comparing one image to someone else's and how they missed the best light or how some uncontrollable factor made their experience not as good as those they have seen. This is where the camera can work against you.. forcing you to feel like your trip was unsuccessful if you don't come back with something "gram worthy."
.

My first experience in the Canyon was similar. At some point you either let this stifle your creativity or you realize the camera is just a small part of the experience.

The effort that goes into creating something is never fully realized on a platform like this... but if it can get people to look at the world differently then it's always worth it.
.

Dappled light in the Alaska range shot from a bush plane a few years back.
It's always better with friends.
The clouds the other night tho! ‚õà

it's nutty how modern the past looks (and quite a contradiction) Everything you see here is found at local charity shops and dates between 40-80 years.  Besides being made properly, it was also with beauty of purpose, allowing for an undeniable timelessness. i can't help but wonder if this all stems from a value system to appreciate everyday, every moment, every puprose? 
in today's modern world, we make everything so quickly JUST to THROW AWAY, i am seeing more and more new expensive things that seem 'cheap' because the lack of value and 'cheap' things that are actually expensive in WASTE, TIME and HUMAN costs. We often wait to value the 'big goals' instead of approaching the everyday 'things' with purpose,wonder, and delight- is this a modern way of value? is this what we want?  because similar to 'things' people become valued with the same system- 'fast friendships, throwaway relationships, expensive but meaningless love? hmmm.... so, my conclusion is that i desire to move forward with lessons of the past, -  anyways, just random personal musings on my personal page, - üåøüôè #sundaymusings #bepresent #gratitude #romancingreality #howwouldyouliketobevalued #howtomoveforwardtogether

Got pregnant. Bought a new home. Got some roses from TH. Provided four new jobs. Finally found an Eames Splint. Did some really cool collaborations with Schott and Babylon. Watched the Warriors fall apart in the Finals. Sold a lot of pins. Sold a lot of jeans. Sold A LOT of t-shirts. Had a thing in Hypebeast mag. Had a thing in Juxstapoz. Did our first interview as a husband and wife team on Maekan. Copped jawns (for the baby).
-----
The last few years have been focused on growing my businesses. 2017 will be about focusing on family.
-----
Thank you for all your support this year. More love, more blessings, more God in 2017!

images.alt:
We said hello at half past one,
all our chores for the morning done;
and as we spoke about our day,
the world began to fall away.

For if my present were an echo of,
a past I can't forget ‚Äî

Then these thoughts are just
an afterthought‚Äî
and I am always in its debt.

A bruise is tender
but does not last,
it leaves me as
I always was.

But a wound I take
much more to heart,
for a scar will always 
leave it's mark.

And if you should ask
which one you are,
my answer is ‚Äî‚Äî
you are a scar.

"Walking Angel"This is really happening. I bite my tongue to try and hold my tears back the moment the music starts. You finally turn the corner with your mom and dad by your side and "WOW!" I scream silently in my head. I couldn't stop thinking to myself that "the woman of my dreams is actually walking towards me to be my wife, God is good and I am truly blessed. I am going to receive the greatest gift the lord can ever give me on earth, a partner for life" 
By now my eyes are locked in and I know if I look at anyone in the audience my eyes would turn into a waterfall. Luckily my focus is set, an angel from above, dressed in all white, beams of light shine outward from her figure, a smile never ending, hair perfectly still, and more beautiful then the sun has ever set. I can hear the steps from her shiny heals hit each stone as she draws closer and closer to me. She is only about 10 steps away and I cant wait to give her the " you may kiss the bride" smooch already. I'm filled with with love in the air with tears of joy are already pouring in my heart, I'm about to break in tears...but then GOD whispers in my ear "she is all yours, i trust you" His words calms my nerves as I take her hand gently from her father and the music fades away. This is the greatest moment of my life. "My Walking Angel" DorothyHoney, I am overly grateful to have you by my side everyday. You have been an fabulous friend, wonderful girlfriend, outstanding fianc√©e and admirable wife. Happy 30th birthday @mshoney you are GOLDEN #30on30 #honeyturns30yearsGOLD

images.alt: Grateful to call myself an earthling. #earthday üåè

Stateside.

People often ask me what my favorite country is. It's an easy answer: The United States of America. I say that with a sense of humility, knowing that our perspectives aren't always shared by all, and a spirit of open mindedness eager to understand the ways of the world through the lens of other cultures. 
I'm blessed to have been born in a country that encourages dreamers to be bold enough to believe they can change the world. A nation that is more an idea of hope than it is a place defined by borders or a people distinguished by the color of their skin. We look completely different from one another but are united by our daring nature to dream. America the beautiful.

It feels good to be back in the home of the brave.
Dreaming on a Dreamliner. ‚úàÔ∏è

#nationalgalleryofart #acreativedc #igdc #vscocam

Deciding to leave my job a few months ago has been the most liberating thing I‚Äôve ever done. I‚Äôve never felt more creative and inspired in my life.
-
In the two years I‚Äôve been back, it‚Äôs been remarkable to see how much my hometown has evolved. When I last lived here in 2009, U Street and H Street were just beginning to come into their own, while Shaw, Union Market, Ivy City, Bloomingdale, and the Navy Yards were places most never even heard of unless you grew up there.
-
DC gets a bad rap for lacking creativity and inspiration. Seeing these neighborhoods undergo a collective renaissance and give birth to flourishing creative platforms like @acreativedc @thisismadeindc @igdc @walkwithlocals @unionmarketdc @unionkitchendc @brightestyoungthings has taught me that's bullshit.
-
While institutions like the National Gallery of Art have been around since before I was born, Monday‚Äôs preview of its newly renovated East Building (which re-opens today) quenched my thirst for art in a new way and showed me just how vibrant and progressive the DC creative community has become as I got to spend the day snapping photos alongside some incredibly talented creatives who I‚Äôve long admired.
-
Two of my new year‚Äôs resolutions were to create art and make a proper @Instagram comeback. I‚Äôve posted nearly as many photos this week as I have in the past year. I realized it‚Äôs because for the first time in a long time, I found creative inspiration again‚Äîalong the walls of the National Gallery of Art and among a community I was finally actively participating in once again. Inspiration I would never have been able to find had I not left my job and opened myself up for new opportunity.
-
I plan on continuing to chase that inspiration throughout my city, with friends new and old. And where I can‚Äôt find it, I hope to help create it.
-
As I‚Äôve told people who have asked me ‚ÄúHow‚Äôs it been going,‚Äù I jumped‚Ä¶ And the net caught me. Thank you to all those who have been my net, helped reawaken my creative spirit, given me opportunities to flex new creative muscles, and reminded me just how much I love not being a passive observer of culture, but an active participant in it.
-

images.alt:
2016 was weird. 2017 will be too. 
What matters is, what we all do. 
Happy New Year, friends.
Got it done! Thanks for all the support. #Run4Refugees

This year for my birthday, I'm going after 30 miles to raise awareness for our current global refugee crisis. Today, there are over 60 million refugees displaced around the globe, 51% who are children. I'd love for you to consider joining me by going for a run and tagging #Run4Refugees and/or checking out the link in my bio and donating to the Refugee Care Collective; a Portland organization that welcomes, teaches English and provides restart kits for incoming families. 
A little bit goes a long way to make life easier for these people who need our kindness, love and help. I'd also recommend checking out what agencies and organizations are in your city to see how you can support.

Thanks for considering, enjoy a run and the holiday season! Did I mention it's below freezing out here! üôà

2016 was a trying year for me. i took a step back for the first time since i was 18 and really thought about what i wanted to do with my life. there were months where i literally stared at the wall and honestly didn‚Äôt know who i was or where i wanted to go, just that i existed. i set a couple of goals and took baby steps towards them. i rebuilt friendships and experienced death close to home, multiple times. i felt what it was like to be human. all those things that i thought mattered before, didn‚Äôt matter much at all. one of the most rewarding times of the last 12 months was watching my kids grow up and being able to spend time with them, every single day. i was able to disconnect from the cyber world, weeks at a time. it brought me immense joy to see my son battle for 5 months to win the regional championship in soccer, and to see my daughter score her first goal. life is about much more than the material mumbo jumbo that makes its way into my feed every time I peruse the gram. it took almost every single hour of 2016 for me to realize that. ...on a lighter note, that digital platform that i spoke about sometime back, the magazine... that‚Äôs on track to launch next month. the apparel project i‚Äôve wanted to build since i was in high school, that‚Äôs in the sampling stages too. things are looking up, just like these fire works outside the window keeping my daughter awake.¬†‚úåüèΩ

images.alt:
"This was the view from our front porch every evening. Huge limestone walls swallowing our tiny cabin. The only cabin in the valley. My girlfriend and I had both recently turned 30. To celebrate, we travelled with a big group of friends to the famed climbing destination El Potrero Chico. By day we would ascent the walls, at one point climbing the longest sport climbing route in North America (Time Wave Zero). By night we would drink mescal, play music, games and laugh. It was one of the best weeks of my life! The magic in this shot in part lives in the wispy clouds streaking over the peak, which were barely visible to the naked eye, and in part in the sharp moonlight rising above the peak behind us." Photo by @tedhesser

DP Robert Richardson, ASC shares his thoughts on shooting LIVE BY NIGHT with @arri_rental's ALEXA 65 system. Read more in the news room on arri.com
#arri #arrirental #alexa65 #livebynight #cinematography #robertrichardson  #inspiringyourvisionsince2017 #arri100 #arribirthday

In the beginning it was two friends and aspiring cinematographers, August Arnold and Robert Richter, who founded a company that would revolutionize the film and television industry. Their collaboration began with a chance meeting at grammar school, where the pair recognized in each other a passion and flair for all things technical. To supplement their pocket money they repaired bicycles and carried out installation work for a local electrical company. As their friendship flourished, so too did their interest in the new-born but fast-evolving technology of moving pictures. #tbt #inspiringyourvisionsince1917 #arri100 #arribirthday

üéØüèÑI demoed the new 2017 Jones Snowboards "Storm Chaser" 147cm. This board was designed by surfboard shaper Chris Christenson, Chris makes amazing surfboard shapes. The fist thing I noticed that it was super fast and light. Board floats really good in powder for a 147cm  because it's wider than a standard snowboard. Board outline had a tapered shape with wider nose and narrower tail this keeps your nose up In powder.  Board has spoon nose. What I really liked was nose transition was long and gradual without being too tall. I loved how responsive and effortless it was to ride in deep powder. Board rides pretty good on the groomers. üëçüëçüèÑ‚ùÑÔ∏èüíØ @jonessnowboards @chris_christenson73 @jeremyjones #StormChaser #JonesSnowboards #powsurfing @timberlinelodge #Timberlodge #MtHood #snowboarding

Leroy ‚ÄúSatchel‚Äù Paige was the first Negro League Baseball player elected to the Baseball Hall of Fame. Paige signed with the Cleveland Indians in 1948 and two days later became the oldest rookie and the first Black to pitch in an American League baseball game.

Paige was born in 1906 in Mobile, Alabama. After the Major Leagues denied him, he started his professional baseball career in the Negro Leagues in 1926. He became one of the league's most famous players. Paige finally broke through to the Majors as a 42-year-old rookie, and was inducted into the Baseball Hall of Fame in 1971 #blackhistory #coloringbook

images.alt:
"Don't look to the impossibles and improbables. There's always a way, you just have to go out there and find it." - #bearwalk ‚†Ä
‚Ä¢‚†Ä
We love a story from @sarablakely that talks about what happens when ideas are new and fresh and young. When others try and help us or guide us they may give us words or wisdom that dissuade us from following passions. Don't. Follow your heart and keep on going. It only becomes impossible when there's no one left to carry on the idea. So you have to keep going you see. You simply have to.‚†Ä
‚Ä¢‚†Ä
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚†Ä
‚Ä¢‚†Ä
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚†Ä
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚†Ä
#filmmaking #adventure #journey #picture #photography #moment #amazing #picoftheday #blue #realmoments #photoshoot @icobar #restaurant

"There is a long road ahead of us, and I don't see the end in site. Now that I think of it, I don't ever want to." - #bearwalk
‚Ä¢
Part #3. So here it is, if you're doing something that excites you, you're not dreading the day or the activity. There is energy in what you do and who you are that spreads through everything. It's incredibly infectious. Conversely, if you are dreading it, whatever it may be, why are you still there? Why do something that makes you unhappy? What's holding you back? If you could be anywhere doing anything, what would it be?!
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢

"If I could chose to be anything in this lifetime, I chose to be alive and enjoy this wonderful life." - #bearwalk
‚Ä¢
Part #2. When we took this image we ventured down this path to follow the horses. We could see them from the road and they ran wild and free. They were the most mesmerizing creatures galloping into the twighlight. And all thoughts just stopped as I watched them run. I could have watched them forever.

abandoned__world.name: Abandoned World
abandoned__world.description: We collect of the most beautiful and fascinating places that have been abandoned. Please follow our friends from:

images.alt: Photo by @mathias_berlin. Follow him for more abandoned shots!  Moss on the ground of the abandoned Fisher Body Plant 21 - Detroit, Michigan. The Piquette Street Fisher Body Plant has been closed since 1984. When it was opened in 1919, it was state of the art. Designed by Albert Kahn, it has reinforced concrete floors and floor to ceiling windows. Six stories high, each floor held heavy equipment. Albert Kahn was responsible for many historic buildings in the Motor City. The early auto industry spawned hundreds of small start-up companies and many of them just built parts. Originally Fisher Body built car bodies for many different automakers, but was bought by General Motors in the 1920s. All GM cars featured "Body by Fisher." Urban artists and explorers have been entering and altering this building with wall art.

images.alt: I'm depressed as hell. I wanted to write some eloquent ass post and thank this man for being the coolest & most selfless president we have EVER HAD (and ever will), but I'm just so so sad. I took this picture in 2012 on campus at UNC for @WRAL and can still remember the incredible energy and excitement in the room to hear him speak. Later that day he appeared on a special taping of "Late Night with @jimmyfallon" - The Roots were roaming campus... everyone was so HYPE and it was just such an electric day filled with good ass vibes. I feel so defeated when I think about who's coming in behind this great man, one who has endured so much BS for our country....Here's to us all holding onto the never-wavering, eternally hopeful spirit President Barack Obama carries with him - it's honestly up to us to keep it going. But for now imma just cry some more. #FarewellObama #Wedidntdeserveyou

That which comprises the harshest burden, a king lifts first and sets down last. A king does not require service of those he leads but provides it to them. He serves them, not they him." -Steve Pressfield 
I worked with a challenging young Malinois this week. As the degree of difficulty in training increases, the more tempting it is to take short cuts. This quote is what keeps me true to our training philosophy. Leadership, not treats, balls or bullshit.

We do not lord over our dogs or buy their obedience. We sweat, bleed and crawl in the muck and shit right along with them. The tougher the challenge, the more valuable your leadership is to your dog. 
Dyas means "pair" in Ancient Greek. We chose this name because it embodies our philosophy. Separately a man and a dog are dangerous. Together they are unstoppable.

I made this Teddy in my #upcycle class today. I watch the news every night and my thoughts and prayers go out to those who are affected by war and homelessness. My class assignment for this final week teaching @sparhawk_school is to inspire the kids to think outside of their little world and think bigger. Give to someone in need and reflect upon your own self worth. Look around you and be satisfied with what you have, because there are plenty of young children in the world that barely have a roof to call home and a toy to call their own. I hope to make as many stuffed animals as possible and send them to a refugee camp where we can make a few children happy. If you feel the same please share with your art teacher or another friend who can do the same. Be a #goodhuman and #care for the world. #moretolife #refugee #wartorn #memories

to all the fly ass people I've met that I've actually been able to connect with as a person in this industry :
I didn't post anything about new years, or christmas, or thanksgiving because it honestly just seemed super cheesy to me at the moment but I do want to take a moment to thank all of the people I've met in my life who have helped me out in this industry, a lot of them which I met thanks to my @arsenic family who so lovingly took me in and helped me mold myself into the presence I am today. When I was first meeting people who were in the modeling/production/designing industry, it felt like a bucket of ice water to my back because of how different they were versus the normal people I know and love, people I grew up with. But to all of the dope funny dorky and silly people I know and love , people who aren't afraid of being their real selves , thank you for fucking existing and for staying true to yourself in an industry that's so full of shallow people pretending to be someone they're not, god BLESS your existence üåπ ‚Ä¢ @bennie.la x @_jannellehill ‚Ä¢

images.alt: We often think about lingerie the same way we consider the facade of a building. Enticing and ornate, we‚Äôre so preoccupied with its decor that we neglect the splendor of its construction. It‚Äôs time to celebrate lingerie in the same way we revere a Mies van der Rohe structure: for what it‚Äôs made of and what it does, not just for what it looks like. ‚Ä¢ Link in bio ‚Ä¢ Photography: @rebeccaastorm ‚Ä¢ Styling: @tubbygorgeous

Padding, golden lace, plastic pearls, and polyester ribbons are no longer the sole contenders for what best represents the wearer between skin and outerwear. Comfort is often lost in superfluous ornamentation. And it is no longer about impressing anybody else. ‚Ä¢ See link in bio ‚Ä¢ Photography: @rebeccaastorm ‚Ä¢ Styling: @tubbygorgeous

Lingerie is the foundational clothing. It adds structure, it protects, it embellishes if desired. As our needs evolve, so does the demand for something functional, comfortable and aesthetically pleasing‚Äîwe no longer have the time or space to differentiate between underwear and lingerie. Photographer Rebecca Storm documents the evolution of lingerie. ‚Ä¢ Link in bio ‚Ä¢ Photography: @rebeccaastorm ‚Ä¢ Styling: @tubbygorgeous

tosanknowsbest.name: Tosan Co.
tosanknowsbest.description: ‚úñÔ∏ècurated goods for the adventure of fatherhood‚úñÔ∏è

images.alt:
I started snowboarding a while ago with my husband, who is really good, and the rest of his alpine-inclined family. I got to the point where I could turn and occasionally not fall getting off the chair lift. So basically, expert shredder level. (Pretty sure that is 100% not the right terminology).
.
But we go so infrequently and I haven't gone since our son was born so I haven't ever really gotten that into it. As in, I wasn't really good so it wasn't that fun. Which is precisely why we get better at things we already have some natural ability in. And those things that need that extra attention, we brush off as lost causes.
.
We are in Tahoe with my cousin and her family. Today, she basically forced me to go snowboarding with her.
.
She said, "Don't be like that. Just come. It will be fine." In the nicest way possible.
.
So the husbands watched the kids. We took two runs. TWO! We practically waited in line to buy lift tickets longer than we rode. The conditions were cold and foggy. I fell getting off the lift the first time and got snow in my pants.
.
AND IT WAS PERFECT.
.
Just that feeling of knowing you pushed past your stupid fears. Asked your ego to shut up for one dang minute. And just let go.
.
It was truly magical and totally real life. Also, I was way better than I remembered (aka EXPERT SHRED).
.
On the car ride home, I told my son that I had been nervous but that I had thought about him being brave learning to snowboard and that had made me brave too. He beamed and told me that next time I could watch him ride down his big hill and that would help me feel happy. And it really did.
.
Sometimes the greatest victories are the quietest. No fanfare or confetti. No flashing lights. Just being content with yourself, in the moment. Magical, I tell you.

I know it seems impossible, but this is a real baby. He's actually this cute. Steezed out in his Tosan Wolf Button! If you don't already follow @jessica_neuner, you're missing out on the coolest mama with the sweetest kiddos. Thanks for the pic!!

We ended up going to three locations with varied landscapes in a 15-square-mile area. By the end of the day, we'd sighted 30 different species of birds, including snow geese, buffleheads, and hooded mergansers.

The Christmas Bird Count (CBC) is one of the most popular and longest-running citizen-scientist projects on the planet. The first CBC involved 27 participants in 25 different locations in the US. Today, there are over 72,000 participants in more than 2,400 locations worldwide.

Some of us at Noah were able to join the Eastern Long Island Audubon Society's Christmas Bird Count for Suffolk County this year. By the end of the day, we'd sighted 30 different species of birds, including snow geese, buffleheads, and hooded mergansers. But the highlight was getting to see a snowy owl perched on the dunes of the beach towards the end of the day.

He and @tyler_warren had just breezed in with a quiver of twin fins to find an unusually quiet lineup complete with tropical drainers that continued into the evening. Kiwi photog @inthedrink spent his entire day alongside slinging his lens from the water. "Everything was looking pretty blown out and mushy, but as the afternoon went on it started to straighten and drop away. We just couldn't believe we'd scored it with this many people and stayed out til we could barely see." #stabfullframe @surfstitch

You know what's annoying? When you ask your friend who is  Gay, Lesbian, Bi or Queer, how they have sex with the same sex.

Talk about intrusive!

As a general rule, you should only discuss someone‚Äôs sex life if they bring up the topic. And even then, try to find a way to approach the subject in a more tasteful way than "How do you do it?!?‚Äù It‚Äôs unfortunate that our sexual education is so poor that we are unable to fathom how sex can even function outside of a heterosexual or cisgendered understanding.  Good sex depends on communication between partners, regardless of gender or sexuality. 
There are plenty of resources that will resolve your confusion so you don't have to interrogate your queer friends. Have a good day üòò

FRONTEER Color Name Inspiration: A natural firefall occurs every so often in Yosemite Valley. Many of our artist friends are creating free artwork to share ahead of the upcoming inauguration like @melkadel we've put the link in our profile to download for easy access
„Éª„Éª„Éª
We're 1 week away from the Women's March On Washington.  Maybe your march will be in a different city, or you'll just be marching on the inside.  But wherever you are, millions of women will be united in strength and numbers.  This is one day after the inauguration of a man who plans to defund Planned Parenthood.  This is just one of the many issues of course, but for me, it sums up the incoming party and how dangerous their tone is.  I made a poster that you can download and print.  This is free, print as many as you want, but don't sell them.  There is a size for your home printer and larger ones if you want to go big:  http://ge.tt/7ZQaSKi2

Open till 6PM. Come hangout.
